cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on predicting adverbial presupposition triggers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a novel attention mechanism, which suggests that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with language generation and discourse systems, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
